The paper deals with unsupervised representation learning for 3D shapes using neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of RNN-based architecture and memory-based approach also suggests a possible connection to graph theory and computational geometry (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of adversarial loss, which is a common technique in generative models and could indicate a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
